        "detail": {
          "TYPE": "Varchar",
          "NULLABLE": false,
          "UNIQUE": null,
          "DEFAULT": null,
          "CHECKS": [],
          "IS_PRIMARY": false,
          "IS_INDEX": false,
          "VALUES": [
            "getPdo() is a static method who get PDO to access to an SQL database",
            "getData() uses PDO to get one result from a database table with a query by prepare it, then execute it & return the result",
            "getAllData() uses PDO to get all results from a database table with a query by prepare it, then execute it & return all results",
            "setData() uses PDO to set one item of a database table with a query by prepare it & return his execution",
            "getModel() is a static method who get the current Model from the table name",
            "listData() lists all results from a database table & return a multidimensional array of the results",
            "createData() creates a new item of a database table from a data array",
            "readData() reads one result from a database table with an id (or another field) & return an array of the result",
            "updateData() updates one item of a database table from a data array & with an id (or another field)",
            "deleteData() deletes one item of a database table with an id (or another field)",
            "setSession() use the array $user to set user alert, or to set user session if $session = true",
            "redirect() creates a header with the url() methods, then exit",
            "url() returns an http_build_query() URL made with the url() arguments",
            "checkAdmin() returns a boolean of some checking tests about the user session",
            "checkArray() checks an Array or a Var of an Array",
            "<PERSON>",
            "getAlert() gets Alert Type or Alert Message",
            "getGet() gets the Get array or a Get value",
            "getSession() gets the Session Array, the User Array or a User Var",
            "getString() returns an User Friendly string after manipulations",
            "parseurl() gets the access parameter from the URL & explode() it to define the controller & the method values",
            "setController() manipulates strings with the controller value to create the good controller name for the new object",
            "setMethod() manipulates strings with the method value to create the good method name for the new controller",
            "run() creates the new controller, call the method on it, then echo() the controller response filtered",
            "setCookie() creates a cookie with setCookie() from the arguments provided",
            "setSession() use the array $user to set user alert, or to set user session if $session = true",
            "<PERSON>",
            "getAlert() gets the Alert array or a Alert value",
            "getCookie() gets the Cookie array or a Cookie value",
            "getEnv() gets the Env array or a Env value",
            "getFiles() gets the Files array or a Files value",
            "getGet() gets the Get array or a Get value",
            "getPost() gets the Post array or a Post value",
            "getRequest() gets the Request array or a Request value",
            "getServer() gets the Server array or a Server value",
            "getSession() gets the Session array or a Session value",
            "<PERSON>",
            "getApiData() returns a json_decode() mixed values of a response from a curl call",
            "getFilename() returns the filename with the path, the name & the extension sets with setExtension() from the arguments provided",
            "getUploadedFile() returns the filename of the uploaded file after moving the the place provided as arguments",
            "getConvertedImage() converts an image with inputImage() & outputImage() from the arguments provided",
            "getExtension() returns a string of the extension with a dot in first (actually only for image extension)",
            "getImageType() returns the exif_imagetype() of the image provided in argument",
            "getInputImage() returns an image resource creates with a PHP image creating function from the image provided",
            "getOutputImage() returns a string creates with a PHP image display function from the image resource provided",
            "getThumbnail() makes a thumbnail with imagescale() & some ImageManager methods from the arguments provided",
            "<PERSON>",
